      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Do not unilaterally change your medication dosage without explicit instruction from your prescribing physician. Suddenly dropping the dose can destabilize your mood and make your bipolar symptoms worse, which is far more dangerous than a little nausea. If the nausea becomes severe, you must monitor it closely, but for a few days, stick to your prescribed regimen and focus on gentle, bland foods. Your body will adjust, but only within the parameters set by your treatment plan.",
